# =====================================================================================
# 0) UTILIDADES: Diebold-Mariano (HAC Newey-West) sin scipy
# =====================================================================================
def newey_west_var(d, lag=None):
    """
    Varianza HAC Newey-West de la media muestral de d_t.
    Retorna var(d_bar) = S / n, donde S es el estimador HAC de la varianza de d_t.
    """
    d = np.asarray(d, dtype=float)
    d = d[np.isfinite(d)]
    n = d.size
    if n < 5:
        return np.nan, int(n)

    d = d - np.mean(d)

    if lag is None:
        lag = int(np.floor((n - 1) ** (1 / 3)))
    lag = max(0, min(int(lag), n - 2))

    gamma0 = float(np.dot(d, d) / n)
    s = gamma0

    for k in range(1, lag + 1):
        gamma_k = float(np.dot(d[k:], d[:-k]) / n)
        w = 1.0 - (k / (lag + 1.0))
        s += 2.0 * w * gamma_k

    var_dbar = float(s / n)
    return var_dbar, int(n)


def dm_test(loss_a, loss_b, h=1):
    """
    Diebold-Mariano con varianza HAC Newey-West usando lag = h-1 (prctica comn).
    d_t = loss_a_t - loss_b_t
    H0: E[d_t] = 0
    """
    a = np.asarray(loss_a, dtype=float)
    b = np.asarray(loss_b, dtype=float)
    mask = np.isfinite(a) & np.isfinite(b)
    a = a[mask]
    b = b[mask]
    n = int(a.size)
    if n < 8:
        return np.nan, np.nan, n

    d = a - b
    d_bar = float(np.mean(d))

    lag = max(0, int(h) - 1)
    var_dbar, _ = newey_west_var(d, lag=lag)
    if not np.isfinite(var_dbar) or var_dbar <= 1e-14:
        return np.nan, np.nan, n

    dm_stat = float(d_bar / np.sqrt(var_dbar))

    from math import erfc, sqrt
    p_value = float(erfc(abs(dm_stat) / sqrt(2.0)))
    return dm_stat, p_value, n


def dm_test_sensitivity(loss_a, loss_b, h=1):
    """
    Diebold-Mariano con lag "de sensibilidad":
      q_sens = min(h-1, floor((n-1)^(1/3)))
    Retorna: (DM_stat_sens, p_value_sens, n, q_sens)
    """
    a = np.asarray(loss_a, dtype=float)
    b = np.asarray(loss_b, dtype=float)
    mask = np.isfinite(a) & np.isfinite(b)
    a = a[mask]
    b = b[mask]
    n = int(a.size)
    if n < 8:
        return np.nan, np.nan, n, None

    d = a - b
    d_bar = float(np.mean(d))

    q_rule = int(np.floor((n - 1) ** (1 / 3)))
    q_h = max(0, int(h) - 1)
    q_sens = max(0, min(q_h, q_rule, n - 2))

    var_dbar, _ = newey_west_var(d, lag=q_sens)
    if not np.isfinite(var_dbar) or var_dbar <= 1e-14:
        return np.nan, np.nan, n, int(q_sens)

    dm_stat = float(d_bar / np.sqrt(var_dbar))

    from math import erfc, sqrt
    p_value = float(erfc(abs(dm_stat) / sqrt(2.0)))
    return dm_stat, p_value, n, int(q_sens)

FILE_PATH = (
    "D:/Documentos Usuarios/sanchezgm/OneDrive - Banco Central de Costa Rica/Escritorio/BCCR/"
    "Cursos y seminarios/PROMIDAT_2025/09 Trabajo Final/Semana 2/data1.csv"
)

df_raw = pd.read_csv(FILE_PATH, delimiter=";", decimal=".")
df_raw = df_raw.loc[:, ~df_raw.columns.str.contains(r"^Unnamed", na=False)].copy()
df_raw["fecha"] = pd.to_datetime(df_raw["fecha"], errors="coerce")
df_raw = df_raw[df_raw["fecha"].notna()].copy()
df_raw = df_raw.sort_values("fecha").reset_index(drop=True)

t_1_vars = [
    "ipp_man", "ip_mpi", "wti", "ismn", "ismr",
    "exp_rd", "exp_re", "exp_tot", "imp_rd", "imp_re", "imp_tot",
    "exp_inf_12_prom", "exp_inf_12_med", "exp_inf_12_merc",
    "brecha_exp_enc", "brecha_exp_mer",
    "exp_inf_12_enc_var", "exp_inf_12_merc_var",
    "tbp", "tpm", "prime", "tcn_var",
    "inf_int"
]
t_2_vars = [
    "w_nom_tc", "w_real_tc",
    "imae", "imae_re", "imae_rd", "imae_sd",
    "cred_mn", "cred_me", "cred_tot",
    "tnp", "to", "ti", "td", "ts",
    "basem_var", "m1_var", "itcer_var"
]
t_3_vars = ["res_fin_gc", "deuda_tot", "deuda_int"]

infl_var = "inf_int"

last_idx_inf = df_raw[infl_var].last_valid_index()
if last_idx_inf is None:
    raise ValueError("No hay valores vlidos en inf_int. Revisa la columna en el CSV.")
df_raw = df_raw.loc[:last_idx_inf].copy().reset_index(drop=True)

df_proc = pd.DataFrame({"fecha": df_raw["fecha"], "target": df_raw[infl_var]})

# 1A) contemporneas (L0) para t_1_vars
for v in t_1_vars:
    if v in df_raw.columns:
        df_proc[f"{v}_L0"] = df_raw[v]

# 1B) rezagos 1,3,6,12 con shifts por disponibilidad (t_1:+0, t_2:+1, t_3:+2)
lags_obj = [1, 3, 6, 12]
all_vars_info = [(t_1_vars, 0), (t_2_vars, 1), (t_3_vars, 2)]

for var_list, extra_shift in all_vars_info:
    for var in var_list:
        if var not in df_raw.columns:
            continue
        for l in lags_obj:
            real_lag = l + extra_shift
            df_proc[f"{var}_L{real_lag}"] = df_raw[var].shift(real_lag)

# 1D) cambio en la inflacin ( inf_int) y sus rezagos 1,3,6,12 (misma disponibilidad t_1)
if "inf_int_L0" in df_proc.columns:
    df_proc["dinf_L0"] = df_proc["inf_int_L0"] - df_proc["inf_int_L0"].shift(1)
    for l in lags_obj:
        df_proc[f"dinf_L{l}"] = df_proc["dinf_L0"].shift(l)

# 1C) recortar hasta el ltimo target observado y limpiar NA
last_idx_target = df_proc["target"].last_valid_index()
df_proc = df_proc.loc[:last_idx_target].copy()
df_proc.dropna(inplace=True)
df_proc = df_proc.reset_index(drop=True)


# =====================================================================================
# 2) FEATURES POR HORIZONTE
# =====================================================================================
t1_contemp_vars = [
    "ipp_man", "ip_mpi", "wti", "ismn", "ismr", "exp_rd", "exp_re", "exp_tot",
    "imp_rd", "imp_re", "imp_tot",
    "exp_inf_12_prom", "exp_inf_12_med", "exp_inf_12_merc",
    "brecha_exp_enc", "brecha_exp_mer", "exp_inf_12_enc_var", "exp_inf_12_merc_var",
    "tbp", "tpm", "prime", "tcn_var",
    "inf_int"
]
contemp_cols = [f"{v}_L0" for v in t1_contemp_vars if f"{v}_L0" in df_proc.columns]
all_feature_cols = [c for c in df_proc.columns if c not in ["fecha", "target"]]

def cols_for_lags(lags_set):
    out = []
    for c in all_feature_cols:
        for lag in lags_set:
            if c.endswith(f"_L{lag}"):
                out.append(c)
                break
    return sorted(set(out))

horizontes = [1, 3, 6, 12]
lags_by_h = {
    1: {1},
    3: {1, 3},
    6: {1, 3, 6},
    12: {1, 3, 6, 12}
}

feature_cols_by_h = {}
for h in horizontes:
    lag_cols = cols_for_lags(lags_by_h[h])
    cols = sorted(set(contemp_cols + lag_cols))

    if h == 6:
        for extra in ["inf_int_L1", "inf_int_L3", "inf_int_L6", "inf_int_L12"]:
            if extra in df_proc.columns:
                cols.append(extra)

    if h == 12:
        for extra in ["inf_int_L1", "inf_int_L3", "inf_int_L6", "inf_int_L12"]:
            if extra in df_proc.columns:
                cols.append(extra)

    if h in [6, 12]:
        if "dinf_L0" in df_proc.columns:
            cols.append("dinf_L0")
        for extra in ["dinf_L1", "dinf_L3", "dinf_L6"] + (["dinf_L12"] if h == 12 else []):
            if extra in df_proc.columns:
                cols.append(extra)

    feature_cols_by_h[h] = sorted(set(cols))


# =====================================================================================
# 3) EXPERIMENTO: tuning pre-2024, testing 2024-2025 (rolling) con ventana mvil fija
# =====================================================================================
fecha_inicio_test = pd.to_datetime("2024-01-01")
indices_test = df_proc[df_proc["fecha"] >= fecha_inicio_test].index

fixed_window = 90

inner_test_size = 12
inner_n_splits = 3

def make_inner_splits(n_obs, test_size=12, n_splits=3):
    splits = []
    end = n_obs
    for k in range(n_splits):
        test_end = end - (n_splits - k - 1) * test_size
        test_start = test_end - test_size
        train_end = test_start
        if train_end <= 0 or test_start < 0:
            continue
        train_idx = np.arange(0, train_end)
        test_idx = np.arange(test_start, test_end)
        splits.append((train_idx, test_idx))
    return splits


# =====================================================================================
# 4) SEARCH SPACE POR HORIZONTE (LASSO)
#     - Se optimiza alpha (fuerza de regularizacin L1)
#     - Pipeline: StandardScaler + Lasso
# =====================================================================================
search_space_by_h = {
    1: {"lasso__alpha": Real(1e-4, 5e-1, prior="log-uniform")},
    3: {"lasso__alpha": Real(1e-4, 8e-1, prior="log-uniform")},
    6: {"lasso__alpha": Real(1e-4, 1.5,  prior="log-uniform")},
    12: {"lasso__alpha": Real(1e-4, 2.5, prior="log-uniform")},
}


# =====================================================================================
# 5) CONTENEDORES DE RESULTADOS
# =====================================================================================
stats_point = {h: {"ae_test": [], "se_test": [], "ae_train": [], "se_train": []} for h in horizontes}

errors_test = {h: {"lasso": [], "rw": [], "ar": []} for h in horizontes}
loss_test = {h: {"lasso_se": [], "rw_se": [], "ar_se": [], "lasso_ae": [], "rw_ae": [], "ar_ae": []} for h in horizontes}

fechas_test = {h: [] for h in horizontes}

preds_test = {h: {"lasso": [], "rw": [], "ar": []} for h in horizontes}
actuals_test = {h: [] for h in horizontes}

best_params_by_h = {}
best_model_by_h = {}

final_models = {}


# =====================================================================================
# 6) CALIBRACIN (una vez por horizonte) pre-2024
# =====================================================================================
print("Iniciando calibracin de hiperparmetros (LASSO) una vez por horizonte usando pre-2024.")
t0 = time.time()

df_train_full = df_proc[df_proc["fecha"] < fecha_inicio_test].copy()

for h in horizontes:
    cols_h = feature_cols_by_h[h]
    if len(cols_h) == 0:
        raise ValueError(f"No hay features para H+{h}. Revisa nombres/rezagos.")

    X_full = df_train_full[cols_h].copy()
    y_full = df_train_full["target"].shift(-h)

    mask = y_full.notna()
    X_tune = X_full.loc[mask].copy()
    y_tune = y_full.loc[mask].copy()

    splits = make_inner_splits(len(X_tune), test_size=inner_test_size, n_splits=inner_n_splits)
    if len(splits) == 0:
        raise ValueError(f"Splits internos vacos para H+{h}. Reduce inner_test_size / inner_n_splits.")

    base_est = Pipeline(steps=[
        ("scaler", StandardScaler(with_mean=True, with_std=True)),
        ("lasso", Lasso(max_iter=20000, random_state=42))
    ])

    opt = BayesSearchCV(
        estimator=base_est,
        search_spaces=search_space_by_h[h],
        n_iter=40,
        scoring="neg_root_mean_squared_error",
        cv=splits,
        n_jobs=-1,
        random_state=42,
        verbose=0,
        return_train_score=True,
    )

    opt.fit(X_tune, y_tune)

    best_params_by_h[h] = opt.best_params_
    best_model_by_h[h] = opt.best_estimator_
    print(f"  Horizonte H+{h}: best_params = {OrderedDict(opt.best_params_)}")

print(f"Calibracin finalizada. Tiempo: {(time.time()-t0)/60:.2f} min.\n")


# =====================================================================================
# 7) EVALUACIN FUERA DE MUESTRA 2024-2025 (rolling) + benchmarks RW y AR(1)
# =====================================================================================
print("Iniciando evaluacin fuera de muestra (2024-2025) con ventana mvil y benchmarks.")
t1 = time.time()

for i in indices_test:
    for h in horizontes:
        if i + h >= len(df_proc):
            continue

        w_eff = min(fixed_window, i)
        if w_eff < 24:
            continue

        cols_h = feature_cols_by_h[h]
        X_all_h = df_proc[cols_h]

        X_train = X_all_h.iloc[i - w_eff : i]
        y_train = df_proc["target"].iloc[i - w_eff + h : i + h]

        if len(X_train) != len(y_train):
            continue

        X_test = X_all_h.iloc[[i]]
        y_test = float(df_proc["target"].iloc[i + h])

        # Refit del LASSO con los mejores hiperparmetros, dentro del rolling window
        params = dict(best_params_by_h[h])
        model = Pipeline(steps=[
            ("scaler", StandardScaler(with_mean=True, with_std=True)),
            ("lasso", Lasso(max_iter=20000, random_state=42))
        ])
        model.set_params(**params)
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)

        yhat_train = model.predict(X_train)
        yhat_test = float(model.predict(X_test)[0])

        # Benchmarks
        rw_pred = float(df_proc["target"].iloc[i - 1])

        ar_X = df_proc["target"].iloc[i - w_eff : i - 1].values.reshape(-1, 1)
        ar_y = df_proc["target"].iloc[i - w_eff + 1 : i]
        if len(ar_y) == len(ar_X) and len(ar_y) >= 10:
            ar_mod = LinearRegression().fit(ar_X, ar_y)
            ar_pred = float(ar_mod.predict([[df_proc["target"].iloc[i - 1]]])[0])
        else:
            ar_pred = float(rw_pred)

        # Guardar
        fecha_th = df_proc["fecha"].iloc[i + h]
        fechas_test[h].append(fecha_th)
        actuals_test[h].append(y_test)

        preds_test[h]["lasso"].append(yhat_test)
        preds_test[h]["rw"].append(rw_pred)
        preds_test[h]["ar"].append(ar_pred)

        e_lasso = float(y_test - yhat_test)
        e_rw = float(y_test - rw_pred)
        e_ar = float(y_test - ar_pred)

        errors_test[h]["lasso"].append(e_lasso)
        errors_test[h]["rw"].append(e_rw)
        errors_test[h]["ar"].append(e_ar)

        loss_test[h]["lasso_se"].append(e_lasso ** 2)
        loss_test[h]["rw_se"].append(e_rw ** 2)
        loss_test[h]["ar_se"].append(e_ar ** 2)

        loss_test[h]["lasso_ae"].append(abs(e_lasso))
        loss_test[h]["rw_ae"].append(abs(e_rw))
        loss_test[h]["ar_ae"].append(abs(e_ar))

        stats_point[h]["ae_test"].append(abs(e_lasso))
        stats_point[h]["se_test"].append(e_lasso ** 2)

        e_train = (y_train.values - yhat_train)
        stats_point[h]["ae_train"].append(float(np.mean(np.abs(e_train))))
        stats_point[h]["se_train"].append(float(np.mean(e_train ** 2)))

        final_models[h] = model

print(f"Evaluacin finalizada. Tiempo: {(time.time()-t1)/60:.2f} min.\n")

print("CUADRO 1: MEJORES HIPERPARMETROS (LASSO, BayesSearchCV) POR HORIZONTE")

df_params = pd.DataFrame(best_params_by_h).T
df_params.index = [f"H+{i}" for i in df_params.index]
print(df_params)

# 9) CUADRO 2: MTRICAS GLOBALES (TRAIN y TEST) POR HORIZONTE

rows = []
for h in horizontes:
    e = np.asarray(errors_test[h]["lasso"], dtype=float)
    e = e[np.isfinite(e)]
    n = int(e.size)

    if n == 0:
        rows.append({
            "Horizonte": f"H+{h}",
            "TRAIN_RMSE": np.nan,
            "TRAIN_MAE": np.nan,
            "TEST_RMSE": np.nan,
            "TEST_MAE": np.nan,
            "TEST_MED_ABS_ERR": np.nan,
            "TEST_MEAN_ABS_ERR": np.nan,
            "n_test": 0,
            "RW_RMSE": np.nan,
            "AR1_RMSE": np.nan,
        })
        continue

    train_mse_mean = float(np.mean(stats_point[h]["se_train"])) if len(stats_point[h]["se_train"]) else np.nan
    train_mae_mean = float(np.mean(stats_point[h]["ae_train"])) if len(stats_point[h]["ae_train"]) else np.nan
    train_rmse_mean = float(np.sqrt(train_mse_mean)) if np.isfinite(train_mse_mean) else np.nan

    test_rmse = float(np.sqrt(np.mean(e ** 2)))
    test_mae = float(np.mean(np.abs(e)))
    test_med_ae = float(np.median(np.abs(e)))
    test_mean_ae = float(np.mean(np.abs(e)))

    e_rw = np.asarray(errors_test[h]["rw"], dtype=float)
    e_ar = np.asarray(errors_test[h]["ar"], dtype=float)
    e_rw = e_rw[np.isfinite(e_rw)]
    e_ar = e_ar[np.isfinite(e_ar)]

    rw_rmse = float(np.sqrt(np.mean(e_rw ** 2))) if e_rw.size else np.nan
    ar_rmse = float(np.sqrt(np.mean(e_ar ** 2))) if e_ar.size else np.nan

    rows.append({
        "Horizonte": f"H+{h}",
        "TRAIN_RMSE": train_rmse_mean,
        "TRAIN_MAE": train_mae_mean,
        "TEST_RMSE": test_rmse,
        "TEST_MAE": test_mae,
        "TEST_MED_ABS_ERR": test_med_ae,
        "TEST_MEAN_ABS_ERR": test_mean_ae,
        "n_test": n,
        "RW_RMSE": rw_rmse,
        "AR1_RMSE": ar_rmse,
    })

df_metrics = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index("Horizonte")

print("\n" + "=" * 125)
print("CUADRO 2: MTRICAS GLOBALES (TRAIN y TEST) POR HORIZONTE | LASSO + RW + AR(1)")
print("=" * 125)
print(df_metrics)

# 12) CUADRO DM: DIEBOLD-MARIANO (Base + Sens)
# =====================================================================================
print("\n" + "=" * 140)
print("CUADRO DM: DIEBOLD-MARIANO POR HORIZONTE | LASSO vs RW y vs AR1")
print("  - Base: NW lag=h-1")
print("  - Sens: NW lag=min(h-1, floor((n-1)^(1/3)))")
print("=" * 140)

dm_rows = []
for h in horizontes:
    se_m = np.asarray(loss_test[h]["lasso_se"], dtype=float)
    se_rw = np.asarray(loss_test[h]["rw_se"], dtype=float)
    se_ar = np.asarray(loss_test[h]["ar_se"], dtype=float)

    ae_m = np.asarray(loss_test[h]["lasso_ae"], dtype=float)
    ae_rw = np.asarray(loss_test[h]["rw_ae"], dtype=float)
    ae_ar = np.asarray(loss_test[h]["ar_ae"], dtype=float)

    dm_stat, pval, n = dm_test(se_m, se_rw, h=h)
    dm_s, p_s, _, q_s = dm_test_sensitivity(se_m, se_rw, h=h)
    dm_rows.append({"Horizonte": f"H+{h}", "Modelo": "LASSO", "Benchmark": "RW", "loss": "SE",
                    "DM_stat": dm_stat, "p_value": pval, "n": n,
                    "DM_stat_sens": dm_s, "p_value_sens": p_s, "NW_lag_sens": q_s})

    dm_stat, pval, n = dm_test(se_m, se_ar, h=h)
    dm_s, p_s, _, q_s = dm_test_sensitivity(se_m, se_ar, h=h)
    dm_rows.append({"Horizonte": f"H+{h}", "Modelo": "LASSO", "Benchmark": "AR1", "loss": "SE",
                    "DM_stat": dm_stat, "p_value": pval, "n": n,
                    "DM_stat_sens": dm_s, "p_value_sens": p_s, "NW_lag_sens": q_s})

    dm_stat, pval, n = dm_test(ae_m, ae_rw, h=h)
    dm_s, p_s, _, q_s = dm_test_sensitivity(ae_m, ae_rw, h=h)
    dm_rows.append({"Horizonte": f"H+{h}", "Modelo": "LASSO", "Benchmark": "RW", "loss": "AE",
                    "DM_stat": dm_stat, "p_value": pval, "n": n,
                    "DM_stat_sens": dm_s, "p_value_sens": p_s, "NW_lag_sens": q_s})

    dm_stat, pval, n = dm_test(ae_m, ae_ar, h=h)
    dm_s, p_s, _, q_s = dm_test_sensitivity(ae_m, ae_ar, h=h)
    dm_rows.append({"Horizonte": f"H+{h}", "Modelo": "LASSO", "Benchmark": "AR1", "loss": "AE",
                    "DM_stat": dm_stat, "p_value": pval, "n": n,
                    "DM_stat_sens": dm_s, "p_value_sens": p_s, "NW_lag_sens": q_s})

df_dm = pd.DataFrame(dm_rows)
print(df_dm)

print("=" * 110)

for h in horizontes:
    if h not in final_models:
        print(f"\nHorizonte H+{h}: (sin modelo OOS disponible)")
        continue

    model = final_models[h]
    cols_h = feature_cols_by_h[h]

    coef = model.named_steps["lasso"].coef_
    s = pd.Series(coef, index=cols_h).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan).dropna()

    if s.empty:
        print(f"\nHorizonte H+{h}: (coeficientes vacos)")
        continue

    top5 = s.abs().sort_values(ascending=False).head(5)
    print(f"\nHorizonte H+{h}:")
    for var, val_abs in top5.items():
        print(f"  - {var:<35}: coef={s[var]: .6f} |coef|={val_abs:.6f}")

from pathlib import Path

# =========================
# EXPORT CONFIG
# =========================
MODEL_TAG = "lasso"  # usa algo consistente en todos los notebooks
OUTDIR = Path("outputs") / MODEL_TAG
OUTDIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

def save_tex(text: str, filename: str) -> Path:
    path = OUTDIR / filename
    path.write_text(text, encoding="utf-8")
    return path

def df_to_latex_file(df, filename: str, caption: str, label: str,
                     index=True, longtable=False, col_format=None,
                     float_format="%.4f", note_source=None, note_notes=None):
    # wrapper pro: booktabs + caption/label + notas (sin pelear con tu LaTeX)
    latex = df.to_latex(
        index=index,
        escape=False,
        longtable=longtable,
        caption=caption,
        label=label,
        float_format=float_format,
        column_format=col_format
    )

    # Opcional: envolver con threeparttable para notas
    if (note_source is not None) or (note_notes is not None):
        # Si longtable=True, conviene threeparttablex; aqu lo dejo simple (tabular)
        wrapped = []
        wrapped.append(r"\begin{table}[!htbp]")
        wrapped.append(r"\centering")
        wrapped.append(r"\begin{threeparttable}")
        wrapped.append(latex.replace(r"\begin{table}", "").replace(r"\end{table}", ""))
        wrapped.append(r"\begin{tablenotes}\footnotesize")
        if note_source is not None:
            wrapped.append(rf"\item \textit{{Source:}} {note_source}")
        if note_notes is not None:
            wrapped.append(rf"\item \textit{{Notes:}} {note_notes}")
        wrapped.append(r"\end{tablenotes}")
        wrapped.append(r"\end{threeparttable}")
        wrapped.append(r"\end{table}")
        latex = "\n".join(wrapped)

    return save_tex(latex, filename)

def save_fig(fig, filename: str, dpi=300):
    path = OUTDIR / filename
    fig.savefig(path, dpi=dpi, bbox_inches="tight")
    return path

# =====================================================================================
# 15) GRFICO 1: EVOLUCIN DEL ERROR PUNTUAL (|error|) + lneas media/mediana
# =====================================================================================
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))
fig.suptitle("GRFICO 1: ERROR PUNTUAL (|y - |) EN TEST 2024-2025 | LASSO", fontsize=16)
axes = axes.flatten()

for idx, h in enumerate(horizontes):
    if len(fechas_test[h]) == 0:
        axes[idx].set_title(f"H+{h} (sin OOS)")
        axes[idx].axis("off")
        continue

    ae = np.asarray(stats_point[h]["ae_test"], dtype=float)
    dates = fechas_test[h]

    axes[idx].plot(dates, ae, marker="o", label="|error| (puntual)")

    mean_ae = float(np.mean(ae))
    med_ae = float(np.median(ae))

    axes[idx].axhline(mean_ae, ls="--", label=f"Promedio |error| = {mean_ae:.3f}")
    axes[idx].axhline(med_ae, ls=":", label=f"Mediana |error| = {med_ae:.3f}")

    axes[idx].set_title(f"Horizonte H+{h}")
    axes[idx].set_xlabel("Mes de evaluacin (t+h)")
    axes[idx].set_ylabel("|error|")
    axes[idx].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    axes[idx].legend()

fig.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.95])
save_fig(fig, "fig_abs_error_test.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

hist = df_proc[["fecha", "target"]].copy()

future_rows = []
for h in horizontes:
    if h not in final_models:
        continue
    model = final_models[h]
    cols_h = feature_cols_by_h[h]
    X0 = df_proc[cols_h].iloc[[-1]]
    mu = float(model.predict(X0)[0])

    f_pred = fecha_base + pd.DateOffset(months=h - 1)
    future_rows.append({"fecha": f_pred, "mean": mu, "h": h})

future = pd.DataFrame(future_rows).sort_values("fecha")

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
plt.title("GRFICO 3: HISTRICA + PROYECCIONES 2026 POR HORIZONTE | LASSO (as-of ltima obs.)", fontsize=14)
plt.plot(hist["fecha"], hist["target"], label="Observada (histrica)", lw=1.5)

if not future.empty:
    plt.plot(future["fecha"], future["mean"], label="Pronstico (LASSO)", marker="o", lw=1.2)

plt.xlabel("Fecha")
plt.ylabel("Inflacin interanual (%)")
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
